  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural and City Grassroots Organizations Building Alliances for Food Sovereignty in the State of Paran&#xE1;.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The central region of the State of Paran&#xE1;, Brazil suffers from severe social, economic and environmental problems that affect rural communities of small farmers, traditional peoples and urban communities. Despite such unfavorable conditions, families work collectively in a rural/urban partnership, networking to construct sustainable solutions, reinforcing their food sovereignty, agroecology, marketing, public policy advocacy, gender and generational equity. In order to succeed, however, these networks need support to ensure they consolidate and improve.  In this project Heifer International will support the dynamics of 15 such networks, thereby benefiting and training over 1,200 rural and urban families. It will educate 50 community development agents, strengthen and create 11 agroecological fairs, four agroecological food distribution systems, as well as systematizing and publishing the region&#x2019;s experience.</narrative>
  </description>
